title: For Sale:  H&K MR556A1 SA 223 Rem/5.56 NATO 16.5
postcontent: A direct descendent of the HK416, the MR556A1 is a semi-automatic rifle developed by Heckler & Koch as a premium level commercial/civilian firearm with match rifle capability. Like the HK416, the MR556A1 is a major product improvement over conventional AR-type carbines and rifles.The MR556A1 uses the HK proprietary gas piston operating system, employing a piston and a solid operating pusher rod in place of the gas tube normally found in AR15/M16/M4-style firearms. This method of operation virtually eliminates malfunctions that are common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area. This is the same key feature critical to the success of the HK416 rifles used by leading military and law enforcement customers. The MR556A1 is produced in the USA using American and German made components. The MR556A1 uses many of the same assemblies and accessories originally developed for the HK416 including the HK free-floating four-quadrant rail system. The HK Free Floating Rail System (FFRS) handguard has four MIL-STD-1913 Picatinny rails and allows all current accessories, sights, lights, and aimers used on M4/M16-type arms to be fitted to the MR Series. The HK rail system can be installed and removed with simple tools and returns to zero when reinstalled. The MR556A1 also has a Picantinny rail machined into the top of its upper receiver for mounting optics and mechanical sights. Unlike earlier prototypes, major subassemblies, including the MR556A1 upper receiver/barrel assembly, are fully interchangeable with other high quality AR-style firearms. MR556A1 upper receiver kits can be used to retrofit competing legacy AR systems. Like the famous HK416, the MR556A1 uses a German-made barrel produced by Heckler & Kochs famous cold hammer forging process. The highest quality steel is used in this unique manufacturing process producing a barrel that provides superior accuracy and long service life.But unlike the HK416, the MR556A1 does not use a chrome-lined barrel. Chrome-lining can sometimes mask bore imperfections and negatively affect accuracy. For the new series of Heckler & Koch semi-automatic MR rifles, HK designers and engineers believe best accuracy comes with an unlined bore. Used with the HK Free Floating Rail System, the barrel does not touch the handguard, ensuring the barrel is truly free-floating for maximum accuracy. The unchromed barrel has an internal profile of 6 lands and grooves with a 1 in 7 inch (178 mm) twist. It is also moderately swagged with a slightly smaller internal diameter at the muzzle end than the chamber end. This feature has a positive effect on bullet accuracy and velocity. The thick, heavy contour 16.5-inch MR556A1 barrel also contributes to its excellent accuracy. A precise enhanced two-stage trigger adds significantly to the accuracy of the MR556A1 and an extended latch charging handle makes operating the rifle with a telescopic sight easier. The retractable buttstock can be locked into a solid, non-moving position by tightening an Allen screw in the bottom of the stock. Special target rifle takedown pins ensure the upper and lower receivers are firmly mated for accurate performance. Designed to function with a wide variety of high quality 5.56 x 45 mm ammunition, the MR556A1 uses a C.I.P. dimensioned chamber (a chamber with dimensions specified by the Commission International Permanente).The MR556A1 also functions reliably with most quality Caliber .223 Remington ammunition. The MR556A1 is being produced with the same commitment to quality as German-made HK firearms. By using joint U.S./German manufacturing, Heckler & Koch leverages the relative strengths of two continents to make the preeminent AR-type firearm, combining the designs innovations of the USA and Germany into one new product. Specifications:- Length, maximum (stock extended): 37.68 in. - Length, minimum (stock retracted): 33.90 in. - Overall Width: 3.07 in. - Height: 9.45 in. - Barrel Length: 16.5 in. - Rifle (without magazine): 8.60 lb. - Magazine (empty 30 round magazine): .31 lb - Magazine capacity: 30 rounds - Trigger Pull: 7.64 lb - Barrel Profile: 6 lands & grooves, right twist, 1 in 7 in - Sight Radius: 14.60 in.

title: For Sale:  Custom Glock 19 - Dual Duty Competition and Concealed Carry / 4 Mags / Multiples Holsters / the works
postcontent:
For sale is a custom Glock 19-pattern pistol built on a Glock frame and LWD stainless slide.
Wilson Combat Match Barrel (http://shopwilsoncombat.com/Match-Grade-Barrel-9mm-for-Glock-19-402-Stainless/productinfo/647/)Stainless slide from Lone Wolf Distributors
Stainless guide rod
Dawson Precision sights with red fiber optic front
Polished and upgraded internals
If you want a gun that can pull dual duty as both a match-grade pistol and as your every day concealed carry, this is it. Legal for 3-Gun matches, IDPA’s new Compact Carry Pistol division, and probably also GSSF and USPSA. Use the same gun in competition that you carry around every day instead of splitting your training between two different weapons.
Willing to throw in an Overwatch Precision match trigger for free. Just haven’t gotten around to installing it yet. I can also install it before purchase if you want, but it shoots real sweet even with the bone stock trigger, which is why I’ve left it so far. I can also change the slide plate cover to a standard, non-engraved one if you don’t like the custom emblem on the back.
The barrel was hand-fitted to the slide and hasn’t even hardly been broken in yet. Round count 150-200 rds. max; still needs a good few hundred rounds to let the barrel hood, slide, and spring all wear in together to give you the perfect balance between tight tolerances and reliability.
Everything fits super tight, but all the moving parts slide around slick as butter. Trigger breaks sweet even in factory stock configuration (as mentioned, competition trigger and springs can be installed on request).
As long as you do your part, this gun will pattern a fist-sized group at 10-15 yards pulling the trigger about as fast as you can get your sights back on target. If you like to shoot steel, this gun will almost feels like cheating. As long as you put the red dot on the black and pull the trigger straight back, you will hear the satisfactory “TING” sound of lead hitting steel following every “BANG.” Anyone who can shoot to the mechanical limits of this gun will be doing very, very well in matches.
Comes with four Magpul G19 magazines, a Stealth Gear Onyx IWB holster, a BladeTech OWB holster, BladeTech magazine holster, Glock Sport holster, Glock Sport magazine holders.
Selling because I need the cash right now a lot more than I need another range toy. Let my poor financial forecasting be your gain.

title: For Sale:  Lionheart LH9NC Compact 9mm  Pistol
postcontent:
The Lionheart LH9 series is an updated and modernized answer to the venerable S&W 5/6906 series by way of our allies in South Korea.
This is the compact version, and comes with custom stippled slim grip panels, ideal for concealed carry and handling in high-stress scenarios.
You can look at all the positive reviews on this gun yourself, including the one done by M.A.C. (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VQYdVx7Oofo). 
Outstanding pistol, and very aesthetically pleasing to boot. Shoots like a dream. Slide moves like it’s on ball bearings. Everything about this gun exudes quality. By far one of the best out-the-box triggers I’ve personally handled.
On that note, this gun has a unique trigger mechanism dubbed “Double Action Plus,” which allows you to “decock” the hammer by simply pushing it forward. This gives your first shot a double action pull length with a single action pull weight, with all subsequent shots in SA mode. Best part: if you neither care for nor understand this feature, you can still use the gun just like you would a traditional DA/SA.

title: For Sale:  CZ 527 Carbine w/ Leupold Scope
postcontent:
This is one of my favorite rifles and it physically pains me to sell it, but I’m hard up for cash and this is what it's come to.
If you’re looking at this listing, chances are you know exactly why this is such an amazing gun. If not, here’s the skinny:
7.62x39 is plentiful and CHEAP. This gun was designed by the Czechs specifically to shoot cheap, steel-cased com bloc surplus ammo. If you do your part, it will pattern under an inch at 100 yards (yes, with 5-rd groups) with steel-cased Tula. I’m not kidding. Contrary to popular belief, 7.62x39 can be very accurate. You just need to shoot it from the right platform.
I’m a big fan of light, fast-handling rifles in wood/laminate stocks that can sling .30 caliber projectiles (see my listing for the Ruger Scout rifle for evidence of this affliction). This gun does all of the above, and looks darn great doing it.
It also has a super crisp and light set trigger, which you can stage for every shot so that the break is much lighter than the standard trigger pull (which is part of what helps the rifle get those sub-MOA groups. This doesn’t mean you get to be sloppy in applying your fundamentals).
Pictured with a Leupold 2-7x scope (which of course comes with their legendary lifetime warranty) and Galco Ching Sling (perfect setup for taking fast shots while on the move using a bolt-action platform).
If you buy the gun, I can also throw in the better part of a spam can of Tula and some brass-cased PMC for a very hefty discount. Let’s say 50% or more off retail, depending on your negotiation skills and friendliness. Also have reloading dies (brand new) for 7.62x39 as well as brass, projectiles, and other components if you can use them.
Asking $650 o.b.o. with sling and scope; $500 without.
